<dl id="n54129p"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54129p">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54129p"> 129(p)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> vedic,</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">3. Le <mark><i>Veda</i></mark>, au sens large, comprend: I. quatre recueils (les <i>V&eacute;das</i>) subdivis&eacute;s en <i>montra</i> (hymnes ou formules rituelles), <i>br&acirc;hmana</i> (trait&eacute;s du sacrifice), <i>&acirc;ranyaka</i> (&laquo;livres des for&ecirc;ts&raquo;; le sacrifice int&eacute;rieur), <i>upanisad</i> (la doctrine m&ecirc;me). <br><font color="green">[3. The Veda, in the broad sense, includes: I. four collections (the Vedas) subdivided into montra (hymns or ritual formulas), br&acirc;hmana (treatises on sacrifice), &acirc;ranyaka ("forest books"; inner sacrifice), upanisad (the doctrine itself).]</font> <small> Ren&eacute; Daumal, <a name="RDLP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RDLP"><cite title="source">Les pouvoirs de la parole</cite></a> (1938) [82]</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
